  "title": "Outlet Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>- At all times, to keep the store organized, clean, and attractive to customers.</p><p>- To oversee the store sales team and other staff members. This includes supervising employees, delegating tasks, evaluating employee performance, managing staff problems, and designing work schedules.</p><p>- Oversee the clinic’s inventory by maintaining stock and purchasing new supplies as needed</p><p>- To greet incoming customers, answer phone calls, and address customer complaints. When customers are ready to check out, assistant outlet managers supervise the cashier to complete sales and collect payments.</p><p>- To achieve assigned target and goals set by company.</p><p>- Ensure cohesive and harmonious working environment at all level in order to achieve Staff Retention rate</p><p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p><p>- At least 1 year proven experience in managing a clinic/beauty salon or similar role</p><p>- Knowledge of the best practices for running a clinic</p><p>- Ability to handle customers' requests and complaints with grace</p><p>- Sales oriented and customer focus</p><p>- Professionalism, independent and initiative with strong self-motivation</p><p>- Excellent communication skills</p><p>- Positive thinking and attitude</p><p>- Ability to establish effective policies and procedures, and maintain high service delivery standards</p>",
